   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "6a25f712",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "1. Online Learning (Streaming ML)\n",
    "✅ What is Online Learning?\n",
    "\n",
    "Online Learning (Streaming ML) is a method where the model learns continuously from incoming data, instead of training once on a full dataset.\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 Data comes one-by-one or in small chunks\n",
    "👉 Model updates incrementally\n",
    "\n",
    "🔁 How it Works\n",
    "New Data → Update Model → Predict → Repeat (real-time loop)\n",
    "No full retraining\n",
    "Model evolves continuously\n",
    "📊 Real-World Examples\n",
    "💳 Fraud Detection\n",
    "Detect suspicious transactions instantly\n",
    "📈 Stock Market Prediction\n",
    "Prices change every second\n",
    "📱 Recommendations\n",
    "Real-time suggestions on YouTube or Instagram\n",
    "💻 Code Example (Online Learning)\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import SGDClassifier\n",
    "\n",
    "# partial_fit allows incremental learning\n",
    "model = SGDClassifier()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Initial training\n",
    "X = [[1], [2], [3]]\n",
    "y = [0, 0, 1]\n",
    "model.partial_fit(X, y, classes=[0, 1])\n",
    "\n",
    "# New data arrives\n",
    "X_new = [[4]]\n",
    "y_new = [1]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Update model\n",
    "model.partial_fit(X_new, y_new)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(model.predict([[5]]))\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 Key: partial_fit() enables streaming updates\n",
    "\n",
    "📌 Key Features\n",
    "Real-time learning\n",
    "Handles streaming data\n",
    "Adapts to concept drift\n",
    "⚔️ 2. Batch vs Online vs Mini-Batch Learning (Deep Comparison)\n",
    "🧠 Core Idea\n",
    "Type\tHow it Learns\n",
    "Batch\tEntire dataset at once\n",
    "Online\tOne data point at a time\n",
    "Mini-batch\tSmall chunks of data\n",
    "📊 Detailed Comparison\n",
    "Feature\tBatch Learning\tOnline Learning\tMini-Batch Learning\n",
    "Training Style\tFull dataset\tIncremental\tSmall batches\n",
    "Speed\tSlow\tFast updates\tBalanced\n",
    "Memory Usage\tHigh\tLow\tMedium\n",
    "Data Type\tStatic\tStreaming\tLarge-scale\n",
    "Adaptability\tLow\tHigh\tMedium\n",
    "Stability\tHigh\tLow (can be noisy)\tBalanced\n",
    "Use Case\tReports, analytics\tReal-time systems\tDeep learning"
   ]
  },
